<TITLE> 30 injured in clash over fishing in Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  At least 30 people were injured in a clash between two groups of villagers over fishing in a pond at Tarash upazila in Sirajganj district on Monday. Of the injured, 18 were admitted to either Tarash Upazila Health Complex or Sirajganj Sadar Hospital. SI Mozzammel Haque, officer in-charge of Tarash police station, told bdnews24.com that there had been a dispute between the local branch of Grameen Bank and Ebrahim Hossain Kalu over the ownership of a pond at Penguari village. Haque said villagers were divided into two groups over fishing in the pond. "The two groups tried to fish there at around 8am and at one stage were locked in a clash. They used homemade weapons during the two-hour clash," he said. At least 30 people of the two groups were injured, the OC said adding additional policemen were deployed to avoid further clashes. He said four persons were arrested in connection with the incident. The injured include Zakaria, 20, Nasim, 20, Montu, 25, Hadiul Alam, 40, Mazid, 50, Rezaul, 35, Hamid, 44, Kudrat, 25, Joynal, 60, Ziaur, 30, Hamida Khatun, 35, Faruque, 30, Mamun, 20, Zia, 35, Idris, 35, Mostafiz, 25, and Montu Sarkar, 28. Identities of the others could not be confirmed immediately. bdnew
